<p><i>Faith, Freedom and Four Paws</i>  by Carolyn Dale Newell</p>  

<p>Have you ever wondered what life is like for a visually impaired person depending on a guide dog for safety? How do guide dogs know when to cross streets? How do they know where to lead their handler? Learn about the intricate details as you travel with Carolyn and Iva on their daily routes. Carolyn shares what she learns about God and Christian living through Iva's eyes. As you read these short tales, you will: Journey through the training process at a guide dog school; Expand your relationship with God through stronger faith; Shake off doubt as you develop a confidence for what God will do in your life; Be encouraged through your own trials. </p>

